      <Field common={false} defaultValue={"host"} enumValues={null} examples={["host"]} groups={[]} name={"host_key"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "host_key"
        }}>{`host_key`}</h3>
        <p>{`The key name added to each event representing the current host. This can also
be globally set via the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/global-options/#host_key"
          }}>{`global [`}<inlineCode parentName="a">{`host_key`}</inlineCode>{`](#host_key)
option`}</a>{`.
See `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "#context"
          }}>{`Context`}</a>{` for more info.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={false} defaultValue={102400} enumValues={null} examples={[102400]} groups={[]} name={"max_length"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={false} templateable={false} type={"uint"} unit={"bytes"} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "max_length"
        }}>{`max_length`}</h3>
        <p>{`The maxiumum bytes size of a message before it is discarded.`}</p>
      </Field>
    </Fields>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "fields"
    }}>{`Fields`}</h2>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-javascript",
        "metastring": "title=\"example log event\"",
        "title": "\"example",
        "log": true,
        "event\"": true
      }}>{`{
  // ...
  "host": "my.host.com",
  "message": "Started GET / for 127.0.0.1 at 2012-03-10 14:28:14 +0100",
  "timestamp": "2019-11-01T21:15:47+00:00"
  // ...
}
`}</code></pre>
    <Fields filters={true} mdxType="Fields">
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["my.host.com"]} groups={[]} name={"host"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "host"
        }}>{`host`}</h3>
        <p>{`The local hostname.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["Started GET / for 127.0.0.1 at 2012-03-10 14:28:14 +0100"]} groups={[]} name={"message"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"string"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "message"
        }}>{`message`}</h3>
        <p>{`The raw message, unaltered.`}</p>
      </Field>
      <Field common={true} defaultValue={null} enumValues={null} examples={["2019-11-01T21:15:47+00:00"]} groups={[]} name={"timestamp"} path={null} relevantWhen={null} required={true} templateable={false} type={"timestamp"} unit={null} warnings={[]} mdxType="Field">
        <h3 {...{
          "id": "timestamp"
        }}>{`timestamp`}</h3>
        <p>{`The exact time the event was ingested.`}</p>
      </Field>
    </Fields>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "examples"
    }}>{`Examples`}</h2>
    <p>{`Given the following input:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-text"
      }}>{`2019-02-13T19:48:34+00:00 [info] Started GET "/" for 127.0.0.1
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`A log event will be output with the following structure:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-json"
      }}>{`{
  "timestamp": <current_timestamp>,
  "message": "2019-02-13T19:48:34+00:00 [info] Started GET "/" for 127.0.0.1",
  "host": "<local_hostname>"
}
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "how-it-works"
    }}>{`How It Works`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "context"
    }}>{`Context`}</h3>
    <p>{`By default, the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`stdin`}</inlineCode>{` source will add context
keys to your events via the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#host_key"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`host_key`}</inlineCode></a>{`
options.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "environment-variables"
    }}>{`Environment Variables`}</h3>
    <p>{`Environment variables are supported through all of Vector's configuration.
Simply add `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`\${MY_ENV_VAR}`}</inlineCode>{` in your Vector configuration file and the variable
will be replaced before being evaluated.`}</p>
    <p>{`You can learn more in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/#environment-variables"
      }}>{`Environment Variables`}</a>{` section.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "line-delimiters"
    }}>{`Line Delimiters`}</h3>
    <p>{`Each line is read until a new line delimiter (the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`0xA`}</inlineCode>{` byte) is found.`}</p>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

